Pizza Margherita

For the pizza dough:

500 grams* Tipo 00 or all-purpose flour (3 ⅓ cups)
8 grams instant or active dry yeast (2 teaspoons)
7 grams sea salt (1 teaspoon)
338 grams warm water (1 ¼ cups + 3 tablespoons)
13 grams olive oil (1 tablespoon)
Semolina flour or cornmeal, for dusting the pizza peel

For the pizza sauce:

1 small garlic clove (1/2 medium)
15 ounces crushed tomatoes or San Marzano tomatoes
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil
½ teaspoon dried oregano
½ teaspoon sea salt

For the toppings:

1/4 to 1/3 cup pizza sauce
3 ounces fresh mozzarella cheese
Parmesan cheese, for topping
Fresh basil leaves, for garnish
